@Node Introduction "Introduction"

  Introduction
  ============

    I've been using magic workbench for ages and I`ve found it be be
    a very nice looking system.  But it does kinda look abit outdated
    these days compared to other operating systems.  So I had a look round
    to see what other icon collections were out there and I found the
    rather great "NewIcons" collection.

    I installed it and it`s great.  Only one problem though.  With
    magic workbench you get a really neat utility called "IconUpdate"

    You basically drop an icon to it, then drop another icon onto it and
    it copied the image from the first icon to the seconds one.  Great!

    It has a few problems though, these are:

      1) does not support copying newicons
      2) if the destination file does not have a .info it does not work.
      3) If you want to update a load of icons you have to keep dragging and
         dropping the first icon and the destination icon for each of the
         icons you wish to update

    New icons comes with a command line program to copy a newicon image
    from one icon to another but it's a CLI based program.  I also found
    another utility that copies the normal icon and the newicon from one
    icon to another but that too was CLI based.

    I wanted the functionality of the two Cli programs but with the
    userfriendlyness of UpdateIcon but without it's limitations.

    Here's where my program comes in!

    With this program you can drag an icon into the "Source" box, then
    drag one or more icons (at a time or individually) to the "Dest" box and
    using the check boxes to the right control what images are copied from
    from the source icon (Normal and/or NewIcon).

@EndNode

@Node Requirements "Requirements"

  Requirements
  ============

    An Amiga with kickstart 3.0 or better (see notes)
    NewIcons installed.
    Icons that need updating :-)

    Notes:
      I wrote this program on an A4000T with WB3.1 and have
      not tested it on any other systems except my A3000 also with 3.1
      It should work down to 3.0 and maybe 2.04.  If it does could someone
      e-mail @{"me" link Author} and let me know please.

@EndNode

@Node Installation "Installation"

  Installation
  ============

    Use the supplied installer script or follow the procedure below.

    Manual Installation
    ===================

    Copy the files "UpdateNewIcon" and "UpdateNewIcon.Guide" using the
    workbench to a folder of your choice.

    That's it.

@EndNode

@Node Usage "Usage"

  Usage
  =====

    Start the program by double clicking it from Workbench

    When it has loaded you'll get a small window with the following items on
    it:

    A Box on the left, labelled "Source"
    A box in the middle, labelled "Dest"
    Some options, labelled "Options" :-)

    The options are:

      Copy Normal
      Copy NewIcon
      Verbose

    And a button labelled "Help"


    To use the program, drag an icon from somewhere on your system to the box
    on the left (Source).  The Icon image should appear in the box if it is
    small enough to fit, if it's not small enough to fit you'll see an
    exclamation mark in the box instead.

    Now drag one or more other icons (at the same time or individually) to
    the box in the middle (Dest) and the icon image in the Source box will
    be copied to all the icons you drag into the Dest box.

    If you keep clicking the Icon in the Source box it will cycle through
    the four icon images, that is: NI Normal, NI Selected, Normal, Selected.
    If the image to be displayed is not present in the icon (i.e. It has
    no newicon image and/or maybe no Selected image the message "NoImage"
    will appear in the box.

    If you enable the "Verbose" check box you'll see information about
    what it happening to the icons as you drag and drop icons to the window.

    You can use the "Copy Normal" checkbox to determine whether the program
    should copy the normal icon image (i.e. the icon you'd see without
    newicons enabled) from the source to the destination icons.

    Likewise you can use the "Copy NewIcon" to control whether the program
    should copy the NewIcon image from the source to the destination icons.

    Normally you'd want to leave both the "Copy Normal" and "Copy NewIcon"
    options enabled (Default).

  Notes
  =====

    It will only display icons less than 64 pixels wide and high in the boxes
    if the image is too large you'll just get a ! in the middle of the box.

    If you are updating a draw icon the directory needs to exist for the
    source icon.  This is a workbench bug/feature, an appwindow message
    does not even get sent to the appwindow!

    If NewIcons has assigned an icon to a device by itself (without there
    being a corresponding disk.info) it is impossible to get the correct
    icon.

    If the icon you are dropping onto the source box is a Disk type and
    is not in the root of a drive with the name of disk.info an appmessage
    does not get sent to the appwindow!

@EndNode

@Node Distribution "Distribution"

  Distribution
  ============

    This program may be included on BBS's, Web Sites, Archive Sites (e.g.
    Aminet) and any storage media you like (even punch tape :-)

    You may NOT modify and redistribute any of the files that make up
    this program without my permission.

    The source code is provided for reference only.  Feel free to learn
    from it if you like.  If you use sections of my code (unalterd or not)
    then please credit me somewhere in your program and let me know via
    @{"e-mail" link Author}.

@EndNode

